1155_1.html|title= Chitra Sarwara, Shamina Shafiq appointed Mahila Congress General Secretaries|date=2018-08-31|work=buisnessstandard|}}</ref> She currently holds the post of National General Secretary and Social Media Incharge of [[All India Mahila Congress]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/rahul-gandhi-appoints-two-more-general-secretaries-of-mahila-congress/articleshow/65628546.cms|title= Rahul appoints two more genral secretaries of Mahila Congress|date=2018-08-31|work=timesofindia|}} </ref>. She has also served as Senior Vice President, Spokesperson and Coordinator for Observers and Co-observers of [[Haryana Pradesh Mahila Congress Committee]]<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.amarujala.com/photo-gallery/chandigarh/mother-s-day-unbelievable-story-of-haryana-mahila-congress-speaker-chitra-sarwara#|title=\u0926\u0947\u0916\u093f\u090f \u090f\u0915 \u092e\u093e\u0902, \u091c\u093f\u0938\u0928\u0947 \u0932\u0940\u0935\u0930 \u0926\u0947\u0915\u0930 \u092c\u091a\u093e\u0908 \u092c\u0947\u091f\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0928|trans-title=Mother&#039;s Day, Unbelievable Story Of Haryana Mahila Congress Speaker Chitra Sarwara|date=2017-05-15|work=amarujala}}</ref>.\n\nShe was elected as a Corporator of [[Ambala]] Municipal Corporation, [[Haryana]], on June 13, 2013.\n\n==Early life and education==\nSarwara is the daughter of former Congress minister [[Nirmal Singh (Haryana)|Nirmal Singh]].<ref name=\":0\" /> She completed her early education at the [[Convent of Jesus and Mary, Ambala]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiastudychannel.com/schools/1266-convent-of-jesus-mary-ambala|title=Convent of Jesus & Mary, Ambala|date=2019-03-23}}</ref> and Bhartiya Public School <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiastudychannel.com/schools/812-bhartiya-public-school-ambala-cantt|title=Bhartiya Public School, Ambala|date=2019-03-31}}</ref> in [[Ambala | Ambala Cantt]] .Later, Sarwara completed her schooling from [[Motilal Nehru School of Sports, Rai]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mnssrai.com/|title=Motilal Nehru School of Sports|date=2015-03-23}}</ref> Sonipat in 1994.\n \nShe was a National Volleyball player, winning many State and National titles as a part of the Rai team. She represented [[Haryana]] in the National School Volleyball Championship in Purnia, [[Bihar]] in 1993 which was won by the [[Haryana]] team.\n\nShe graduated from [[National Institute of Design]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nid.edu/institute/campuses/ahmedabad.html|title=National Institute of Design|date=2013-03-11}}</ref>, [[Ahmedabad]] in 2000 as an Industrial Designer specializing in Furniture design.\n\n==Career==\n\nShe has worked with Tesseract Design<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tesseractdesigns.in/|title=tesseract designs|date=2005-07-11}}</ref> in [[Bangalore]] and then went on to [[Idiom Design and Consulting]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idiom.co.in/|title=Idiom Design and Consulting|date=2007-05-21}}</ref> [[Banglore]]. In [[Delhi]] she worked as an independent Design consultant and eventually as Design Head of the [[Delhi]] office of [[Idiom Design and Consulting]].\n\nWhile with Idiom Design and Consulting, she was Design Manager for developing the [[2010 Commonwealth Games]] Image and Look program which involved developing the games branding from Logo to application of Image and Look program across city and collaterals.\n\nSarwara quit the [[BJP]] in October 2019 in protest after Jasbir Singh Malour was chosen as the party's candidate for a congressional seat instead of her father [[Nirmal Singh (Haryana)|Nirmal Singh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/politics/haryana-polls-with-ex-minister-nirmal-singh-daughter-chitra-sarwara-in-fray-contest-gets-tougher-for-congress-in-ambala-7513281.html|title=Haryana polls: With ex-minister Nirmal Singh, daughter Chitra Sarwara in fray, contest gets tougher for Congress in Ambala|website=Firstpost|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> She criticized the party for what her and her father described as a betrayal, and backed him as an independent nominee representing [[Ambala City (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Ambala City]] in the congressional race.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Sharma|first=Aman|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/fault-lines-show-congress-to-battle-rebels-in-10-seats/articleshow/71589602.cms|title=Fault lines show, Congress to battle rebels in 10 seats|date=2019-10-15|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/politics/haryana-polls-with-ex-minister-nirmal-singh-daughter-chitra-sarwara-in-fray-contest-gets-tougher-for-congress-in-ambala-7513281.html|title=Haryana polls: With ex-minister Nirmal Singh, daughter Chitra Sarwara in fray, contest gets tougher for Congress in Ambala|website=Firstpost|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nSarwara also ran for a congressional seat representing the [[Ambala Cantonment]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/cities/rebel-father-daughter-duo-pushes-congress-to-its-worst-show-in-ambala-city-and-ambala-cantt/story-6IocoIeqjEZtguvuglkvmJ.html|title=Rebel father-daughter duo pushes Congress to its worst show in Ambala City and Ambala Cantt|date=2019-10-25|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> She lost to [[Anil Vij]], coming in second with a total of 36.48% of the votes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/elections/haryana-assembly-polls-2019-ambala-cantt-election-result-live-counting-bjp-anil-vij-congress-venu-singla-557227|title=Ambala Cantt Constituency Result Live: BJP's Anil Vij wins by 20,165 votes|last=Mamtany|first=Sidhant|date=2019-10-24|website=www.indiatvnews.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n==Political career==\n\n* In 2013, Elected as an independent Municipal Corporator from [[Ambala Cantt]], a newly formed Corporation.\n\n* In March 2015, she joined [[Haryana Pradesh Mahila Congress Committee]] as a State Coordinator for Observers & Co-observers of Rohtak- Karnal Division (Minus Bhiwani and Kaithal) and as a spokesperson under the leadership of the dynamic State President Smt. [[Sumitra Chauhan]].\n\n* In 2016 she was appointed Senior Vice President of the [[Haryana Pradesh Mahila Congress Committee]].\n\n* In 2017 she was appointed Social Media Incharge for [[All India Mahila Congress]] during the tenure of [[All India Mahila Congress|AIMC]] Pres Smt. [[Shobha Oza]] and started the first concerted effort by the Organisation to build its online presence through Website and other social media platforms.\n\n* 13th Dec 2017: [[All India Mahila Congress]] Website was launched by [[Indian National Congress]] President Sh. [[Rahul Gandhi]] during a [[Mahila Congress]] workshop - '''The Way Ahead''', organised under the aegis of [[Sushmita Dev]], President [[All India Mahila Congress|AIMC]].\n\n* 2018 appointed as Secretary, [[All India Mahila Congress]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/news/HAR-AMB-OMC-MAT-latest-ambala-news-041003-1230387-NOR.html|title= Chitra Sarwara appointed Secretary of All India Mahila COngress|date=2018-03-08|work=danik bhaskar|}} </ref> .\n\n* Coming from a Design background and with immense interest in developing identity and organisations, Chitra picked up the long standing project of developing an individual identity/logo for [[Mahila Congress]]. \n\n* 7th August 2018, [[Mahila Congress]] Logo and Flag <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/news/latest-ambala-news-020523-2419783.html|title= Rahul Gandhi launched Logo and Flag designed by Chitra|date=2018-08-07|work=danik bhaskar|}} </ref> was launched by [[Indian National Congress|INC]] President Sh. [[Rahul Gandhi]] during the '''Mahila Adhikaar Sammelan'''.\n\n* 30th Aug 2018 appointed as General Secretary, [[All India Mahila Congress]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/rahul-gandhi-appoints-two-more-general-secretaries-of-mahila-congress/articleshow/65628546.cms|title= Rahul appoints two more genral secretaries of Mahila Congress|date=2018-08-31|work=timesofindia|}} </ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Indian National Congress}}\n{{All India Mahila Congress}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Indian National Congress organisations]]\n[[Category:Women's wings of political parties in India]]\n[[Category:All India Mahila Congress]]\n[[Category:India political party templates|All India Mahila Congress]]\n[[Category:Indian National Congress|\u03c4]]\n[[Category:Socialist party templates]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n", "name_user": "Tayi Arajakate", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chitra_Sarwara"}
